Third, I examine income. On the one hand, one should anticipate households with a lower income to engage in more cross-border shopping given their higher import elasticities (see Auer et al. 2024) and the larger share of their income dedicated to groceries. For instance, households in the top income quintile allocate only 1.7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
